{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strong"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples"},{"code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Styles","anchor":"Styles"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pressed"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hovered"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"enabled"}]},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"type":"text","text":" values of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SoshTheme"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WireframeTheme"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Colored surface","anchor":"Colored-surface","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Specific behavior","anchor":"Specific-behavior","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Orange Compact","anchor":"Orange-Compact","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sosh","anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Wireframe","anchor":"Wireframe","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}]}],"name":"Version","type":"aside"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}]}],"name":"Since","type":"aside"}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Button is a UI element that triggers an action or event, and is used to initiate tasks or confirming an action."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Button appears in different layouts, styles and states to